last_episode_to_air.name: Local Reputations
last_episode_to_air.overview: Darnell "SuperChef" Ferguson welcomes four chefs to settle some turf wars with $10,000 and their personal knives on the line. In the first battle, Northern California caterer Lamont Perriman calls out rival caterer Terry Braggs for creeping in on his territory, wooing clients with his personality rather than talent and hard work. In the second battle, Top Chef alum Lee Anne Wong challenges James Beard nominee Sheldon Simeon to redeem herself after he judged her off Alex vs. America for her Hawaiian dish. She wants to prove to Sheldon, as well as judges Chris Cosentino and Antonia Lofaso, that she belongs on the list of Hawaii's best chefs.

overview: Darnell "Superchef" Ferguson invites superstar chefs to settle their disputes in a one dish, winner-takes-all heavyweight battle. The victors leave with $10,000, a prized knife from the losing chef's knife roll and bragging rights for life!

episodes.name: Surf-and-Turf Wars
episodes.overview: In the first match, the acclaimed Chef Matt Klum calls out his former boss and restauranteur, Chef Dana Downs, to prove she made a huge mistake letting him go 10 years prior. In the second match, the renowned Chef Danny Wilson challenges Food Network Star runner-up and Beat Bobby Flay winner Jay Ducote in a head-to-head battle to prove, once and for all, who is the real deal when it comes to Southern cuisine. In the end, judges Catherin McCord and Justin Sutherland choose who will leave the arena with a $10,000 cash prize, a special knife from the losing chef and, most importantly, bragging rights for life!

episodes.name: GGG Grudges
episodes.overview: Darnell "SuperChef" Ferguson invites four Guys Grocery Games OG's to put their knives on the line as judges Aarti Sequeira and Brooke Williamson settle the chefs' festering grudges. In the first battle, celebrity host Catherine McCord calls out fellow GGG judge and food critic Troy Johnson for steamrolling the judging panel. In the second battle, legendary chef Antonia Lofaso can't wait to show her fellow GGG champion, chef Brian Malarkey, that his victory over her in a past competition was a fluke and that she's the real winner, then and now.

episodes.name: Frenemy Feuds
episodes.overview: Darnell "SuperChef" Ferguson welcomes four friends with grudges to battle it out and impress judges Brian Malarkey and Lee Anne Wong for $10,000, their favorite chef knives and bragging rights for life. Chef Matt Jordan, an executive chef for a global food company, still carries a chip on his shoulder because Chef Gio Osso wouldn't promote him to Chef de Cuisine at his award-winning restaurant seven years ago. Then, celebrity Chef Joe Sasto resents his best friend Iron Chef Justin Sutherland's habit of failing to prep their events and arriving only when it's time for the accolades.

episodes.name: All Stars Settle the Score
episodes.overview: Darnell "SuperChef" Ferguson prepares the arena as long-time rivals compete in two epic all-star battles for the favor of judges Eric Adjepong and Stephanie Izard. In the first match, Chef Nate Appleman takes on Chef Amanda Freitag to show the world that he's ready to join the elite corps of chefs who compete on Tournament of Champions. In the second match, there's old beef to settle when Chef Jonathon Sawyer challenges Chef Chris Cosentino for the title of America's Meat Master.

episodes.name: Students vs. Masters
episodes.overview: Darnell "SuperChef" Ferguson welcomes two pairings of superstar mentors and their mentees to his arena to settle their grudges in front of judges Joe Sasto and Aarti Sequeira with $10,000 and their personal chef knives on the line. In the first match, Hawaiian transplant Chef Shaymus Alwin calls out Hawaiian native Chef Colin Hazama to prove he is the master of Hawaiian cuisine. Then, Top Chef alum Chef Joe Flamm calls out his former boss, Iron Chef Stephanie Izard, in a deep dish battle for Chicago turf.
